LIBER XXIII. CAP. XLI. 57

CHAPTER XLI.

Hasdrubal, the Carthaginian Genesi-al, made Prisonor, with two Cartha· ginian Nobles, Hanno and Mago. Hostis falls in Battle. Hamspicora fleas, and kills himself. Manlius obtains Possession of Cornus, the City to which the Remnant of the Army had fled. Other Cities surrender. Required to give Hostages, and aro mulcted in Moncy and Corn. Manlius returns to Caralesu and thence sails to Rome. T. Otacilius crosses into Africa and ravagcs the Carthaginian Territory. Pro· ceeding towards Sardinia, he falls in with Hasdrubal‘s Fleet returning Home. Takes seven Ships. Remainder of the Fleet dispersed. Bomilcar, with Reinsorcemonts and Supplies from Carthago, proceeds to Locri (in Bruttium). Appius Claudius hastily leads his Army to Messana, with the View of erushing him while off his Guard. Bo- milcar already departed to join Hunno. The Locrians close their Gates against the Romans. Ap. Claudius returns to Messana—nc. 215.
